edu.umd.cs.guitar.graph.plugin

Class EFG2ECIG

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umd.cs.guitar.graph.plugin.G2GPlugin
      • edu.umd.cs.guitar.graph.plugin.EFG2EIG
        • edu.umd.cs.guitar.graph.plugin.EFG2ECIG

  • public class EFG2ECIG
extends edu.umd.cs.guitar.graph.plugin.EFG2EIG
    Read an input graph and generate the corresponding output graph. The edges added to the output graph are a subset of the input graph. They are the edges present in the ECIG data read from the ECIG data file. Note: If the input graph contains duplicate events, then the output graph will contain the same. Conversions: 1. EFG -> ECIG As of now ALL events from the input graph are transferred to the output graph. This needs to be pruned.
    Author:
    Ishan Banerjee
